This location for Jupiter's is basically night and day from their Village at the Crossing location. It's more of a dive bar feel. There are 5 pool tables and a few seating options if you're there for a pizza. The pool tables are well maintained and have the normal above table lighting. The bar is fully stocked to accommodate most all drink requests. But the look and feel will always be that of a very common bar. Nothing stands out, except maybe the bathrooms which I don't recommend using while sober. It's the original and people will always love it for that, but it doesn't have much more going for it.
